docs.abstract: The race is over. The race to the bar is on.
docs.snippet: The race is over. The race to the bar is on.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Senator Elizabeth Warren dropped out of the presidential race on Thursday, it was a devastating blow for her supporters and the 1,000-some staff members she had hired from coast to coast. But within hours, hundreds of alerts began popping up on their phones: emojis of whiskey pours, clinking champagne flutes, sloshing beer mugs, martinis and red wine glasses.

headline.main: Their Campaign Jobs Just Dried Up. And on Venmo, the Drinks Are Flowing.
